{
  "texts": [
    "In the third and final step, for each word within the article (n ∈ {1, …, N d }), each topic is selected through sampling from a multinomial distribution over d.",
    "In this study, the modeling process involved three primary steps.",
    "First, terms from titles, abstracts, and keywords, were pre-processed by removing numbers, punctuation, and stop-words.",
    "Next, using the term frequency-inverse document frequency technology, unimportant words were filtered out based on a threshold of 0.05.",
    "Within the pool of potential models encompassing topic quantities spanning from 5 to 30, models with higher performance in terms of semantic coherence and exclusivity were manually compared and evaluated."
  ]
}